The Adamawa/Taraba Area Command of the Nigeria Customs Service (NCS), has raided a residential building along Doubeli by-pass in Jimeta and seized undisclosed number of bags of foreign rice. The spokesman of the Command, ASC Muawuya Abubakar said, the seizure was made possible through an informant who disclosed the location of the house. Abubakar said the bags of rice could be smuggled through porous border, saying the command would not relent in its efforts to eliminating contraband goods in the state. He said the operation was conducted inline with the mandate of the service, urging members of the public to desist from smuggling activities. “We got information from one of our informants that foreign rice is been hoarded in a residential building. “We are doing our best and whosoever is arrested in connection must face the wrath of the law.” The house would be under lock and key, pending investigation into the matter the spokesman added. 